{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_bubley_ver02/data/sn82016181/00529040088/1945092101/0714.xml":{"full_text":"IS -Till WASHINGTON DAILY NFWS. FRIDAY. SKPTEMBXR 81, 1445\nCommon Man Left\nin New Wallace Plan\nBy United Press\nGovernment reorganization under President Truman reached\nout today to the Commerce Department, where Secretary Henry\nA. W allace announced plans to increase his agency\u2019s aid to busi\nness and bring business and Government closer together.\nThe alterations go hand-in-hand*\nwith recent changes in the Labor De\npartment, designed to make that body\nmore serviceable to the nation's work\ners. Wallace said one of his chief aims\nis to have his department pull its full\nload\u201d toward achievement of 60.000.000\nJobs by 1950.\nMORE BUSINESS AIDS\nKey to the reorganization plan is\nthe aim of stepping up America\u2019s for\neign trade and providing more techno\nlogical. statistical and management aid\nparticularly to small business.\nHe will'seek three new assistant sec\nretaries to concentrate on the problems\nof international trade, industrial econ\nomy and .small business.\nTo aid business here at home Wal\nlace proposed:\n1. A strong balanced program to pro\nvide business and government with\nstatistics, centering around a complete\ncensus every five years, greatly expand\ned to include housing, labor, agricul\nture, manufactures, mineral industries,\nb isiness, consumer income and buying\npower.\n2 A complete analytical program to\ngive business and Government infor\nma'ion on the economic situation and\nbusiness outlook.\nTO EQUAL FARM AID\n3. Aids and service pn technical, en\ngineering and scientific problems. The\nsame sort of service given to farmers\nby the Agriculture Department which\nWhoa! American\nG2s Can't Marry\nGermans After All\nBy United Press\nBERLIN. Sept. 21\u2014The U. S. Group\nCouncil announced today that there\nwas no intention of allowing marriages\nbetween service personnel and German\ncivilians in the American Occupation\nZone.\nThe announcement apparently blast\ned any hopes that any Gls might har\nbor for taking German wives. The\nAllied Control Council yesterday lifted\nall restrictions on such marriages, sub\nject to the individual decision of each\noccupation zone commander.\nIt was understood that there was no\nprospect of lifting the marriage ban\nin the American Zone, at least in the\nforeseeable future.\nThe relaxation of the fraternization\nrule yesterday becomes effective Oct.\n1 The new decision also left to the\nzone commanders the matter of billet\ning troops with German families.\nCaswell Custom Tailoring Assures\nSuH Perfection\nYes. you are as- 9\nsured of perfect\nfit and style-right s C j\nsuits and coats at y\nCaswell\u2019s because\nof the perfection i\nin tailoring to >^4\nyour individual 1\ntaste and fit. L y\n29 50 ar\nCaswell tailors are\nexpert craftsmen as-/\nsurma you of qualnvU\nworkmanship The\nnew fall woolen*.\nplaids fine shetlands 212-^4*\nand gabardines ha\\e T J\narrived Make your\nselection today\nCASWELL\n941 Penn. Ave. N.W.\nOpp. Dept. Justice\nOpen S A M to A PM\u2014Thursday\nand Saturday Vntit 8:80 I\u2019 M.\nMr. Wallace headed from 1933 to 1940.\n4 Management aids to busines, ori\nented to the needs of small as well\nas large business.\n5. Strengthening of the technical\nservice functions of the department\nto promote civil, commercial and pri\nvate aviation thru the CAA.\nWallace also plans the expansion of\nthe Weather Bureau and the Coast\nand Geodetic Survey, as weli as es\ntablishment of a science advisory com\nmittee to recommend on the develop\nment of scientific activities.\nDiamond and Ruby\nCOCKTAIL RING\nA handsome creation set with\na diamond and genuine rubies.\n14-k. rose gold mount- S X ^.75\ning. 4iJ\nPius 20% Tax\nfor value of real dittinction\u2014 A I i t I 1 t Wfe\nPay Weekly. Semi-Monthly\nMonthly.\nLADIES\u2019 BENRUS\nA new creation of typical Benrus\nquality and accuracy. s^^J,7s\n15 jewels. Uw\nTax Included\n91.25 Week!\nGift headquarter! for over\ntea* men. Mailing deadline\nit Oct. 15th.\nJudge Refuses\nDirected Verdict\nfor Lieut. Epes\nCOLUMBIA. S. C., Sept. 21\u2014Judge\nA. L. Gaston today rejected a defense\nmotion for a directed verdict of ac\nquittal in the trial of wealthy Samuel\nC. Epes, charged with slaying his wife.\nGaston ruled that the guilt or inno\ncence of the defendant must be deter\nmined by the jury.\nThe defense plea for a directed ver\ndict had been made immediately after\nthe prosecution rested its case.\nGoing, Going, Gone!\nTrucks \u2014300 of them, big ones, little\nones, some station wagons\u2014will be in\ncluded in the second lot of surplus\nproperty to be sold this month by the\nOffice of Surplus Property at Ft.\nMeade Sept. 27, starting 11 a. m.\nMEN\u2019S HELBROS\nHandsome, manly, square case with\nguaranteed movement. $0^.75\nTax Included A 4\n91.25 a Week!\nCuba Waives Visas\nfor U. S. Citizens\nMIAMI, Fla., Sept. 21\u2014Cuba has been\nadded to the list of Latin American\ncountries which do not require pass\nports from Americans entering the\ncountry.\nThe Cuban commissioner of immi\ngration notified Pan American Airways\nyesterday that the new rule would be\nin effect Immediately. The announce\nment said that several other South\nAmerican countries were expected to\nchange passport regulations soon.\nNassau, in the Bahamas, Mexico and\nGuatemala do not require Americans\nto have passports now.\nTB'ers Hospitalized\nTwo of seven TB patients for whom\nAlexandria has been unable to find\nhospitalization today are in Catawba\nand Piedmont sanitaria, as result of\naction by the Alexandria TB Associa\ntion. Four others who could not gain\nadmittance to State institutions have\ndied in the city during the past five\nmonths.\nDIAMOND\nCOMBINATION\nHandsomely engraved bands of 14-\nkarat yellow gold that match per\nfectly and a sparkling S^[E.OO\ngenuine diamond. 40\nHut 20% Tax\n91.25 a Week!\n35-Pc. Dinner Set\nComplete service for six. 